<Document>
  <name>Brazos County — Unmapped Historical Markers</name>
  <description>THC markers in Brazos County without an HMDB id (isMissing excluded). 26 with THC coords; 0 geocoded from address; 6 omitted (no usable address).</description>
  <Placemark>
    <name>Alexander Methodist Chapel</name>
    <description><![CDATA[From the intersection of SH 6 and FM 974 (North Bryan) take FM 974 north approximately 5.3 miles to Alexander Rd., then NW on Alexander Rd. approximately .9 mile to Alexander Cemetery Rd., then on cemetery road approximately .1 mile.<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> Bryan<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> Organized in 1854 by Robert Alexander, Circuit Rider. First church built of hand-hewn logs in 1856 by early settlers, George Fullerton, Hugh Henry, Jim Walker, John Walker, E.W. Thompson and others. Ten acres of church land donated by Eliz Boatwright and John Singleton was deeded to the following trustees: James Walker, William Lawrence, John B. Wallace, William Glass and Harvey Mitchell. Second church was built in 1908 - W.D. Gardner, Pastor. Third church was built in 1939 - Willard Smith, Pastor.]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-96.384222,30.78162,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
